<https://thesyndicate.com/> a <http://schema.org/WebPage>;
  <http://schema.org/url> <https://thesyndicate.com/>;
  <http://schema.org/name> "The Syndicate";
  <http://schema.org/datePublished> "";
  <http://schema.org/description> "[Jason Calacanis has invested in over 300 startups in the past decade, was Sequoia Capital&#x27;s first Scout, and is the author of the book ANGEL. He hosts two podcasts, This Week in Startups and All-In, and is a regular contributor to CNBC.]";
  <http://schema.org/thumbnailUrl> "https://super-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/42db5453-98ce-4aa0-a257-36c2aa17ba98/uploads/cover/e7a6e6e5-d301-4fea-8a15-e6219607e4f9.png" .

<https://calacanis.substack.com/> a <http://schema.org/WebPage>;
  <http://schema.org/url> <https://calacanis.substack.com/>;
  <http://schema.org/name> "Jason Calacanis on Startups | jason@calacanis.com | Substack";
  <http://schema.org/datePublished> "2021-05-31T00:00:00";
  <http://schema.org/description> "[Thanks for reading The Jason Calacanis Newsletter! Subscribe for free to receive new posts and support my work. ... Rachel: My favorite episode was E1652. Jason and Molly spoke with Coffeezilla (1:11) about the latest (alleged) Logan Paul scam involving CryptoZoo., Brian: My favourite episode this week has to be E1649: SpaceX valued at $137B, Starlink&#x27;s massive market, Shopify purges meetings. But more specifically, when Jason and Molly give an example of a bottom-up TAM for Starlink. (16:16) I find it extremely valuable when they give real-world examples!, Jon: My favorite episode this week is E1651. I particularly enjoyed the segment where Jason and Molly dived into the minds of Microsoft and Google. The debate of who will gain ground was engaging and entertaining! Also, watching AI technology advance and what we may see down the road with these advancements is especially thought-provoking., Keith Rabois on 2023 macro outlook, startup valuations, founder advice, ChatGPT vs Google | E1650 Multiple time guest and friend of the pod Keith Rabois is back! Jason and Keith talk 2023 macro outlook (1:00), big tech&#x27;s impact on startups (10:01), advice for founders (18:24), Meta&#x27;s risky VR bet (27:22), ChatGPT vs Google (39:05), and more!]";
  <http://schema.org/thumbnailUrl> "https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:best,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fcalacanis.substack.com%2Ftwitter%2Fsubscribe-card.jpg%3Fv%3D1618231118%26version%3D9" .

