<https://www.bigspeak.com/speakers/jason-calacanis/> a <http://schema.org/WebPage>;
  <http://schema.org/url> <https://www.bigspeak.com/speakers/jason-calacanis/>;
  <http://schema.org/name> "Keynote Speaker Jason Calacanis Speaking Fee and Information";
  <http://schema.org/datePublished> "2018-06-24T16:47:08";
  <http://schema.org/description> "[Jason Calacanis is a top business speaker and tech thought leader known as the “greatest angel investor.” His book Angel: How to Invest in Technology Startups: Timeless Advice from an Angel Investor Who Turned $100,000 into $100,000,000 was an Audible bestseller., Jason Calacanis is a member of the trusted inner circle for Elon Musk and possibly the next CEO of Twitter. Jason authored the best-selling book Angel: How to Invest in Technology Startups: Timeless Advice from an Angel Investor Who Turned $100,000 into $100,000,000., Jason authored the best-selling book Angel: How to Invest in Technology Startups: Timeless Advice from an Angel Investor Who Turned $100,000 into $100,000,000. Calacanis has invested in over 300 early-stage startups including several that have achieved billion-dollar valuations, including Uber and Thumbtack., In this fireside chat with Jason Calacanis, audiences will dive deep into the world of Silicon Valley, tech companies, and angel investing. Jason shares stories about his journey from tech company creator to tech company angel investor. Learn the secrets of Silicon Valley and the process Jason uses to evaluate tech companies and their founders when investing.]";
  <http://schema.org/thumbnailUrl> "https://www.bigspeak.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Jason-Calacanis-e1656088661344.jpeg" .

<https://earlynode.com/profiles/jason-calacanis> a <http://schema.org/WebPage>;
  <http://schema.org/url> <https://earlynode.com/profiles/jason-calacanis>;
  <http://schema.org/name> "What is Jason Calacanis’s net worth in 2023? | Bio &amp; Career – EarlyNode";
  <http://schema.org/datePublished> "";
  <http://schema.org/description> "[The net worth of Jason Calacanis is approximately $100 million making up the smallest portion of the All In Podcast net worth. In October 2005, he successfully sold his first company, Weblogs, Inc., to AOL for a sum of $30 million. Afterward, he went on to establish several online businesses such as Silicon Alley Reporter and Mahalo.com, a web directory., Jason Calacanis, is an American entrepreneur, investor, blogger and the co-founder of LaunchCapital, a venture capital firm specializing in early-stage investments. He is also the co-host of the podcast called “This Week in Startups,” which focuses on startups and entrepreneurship. Jason Calacanis was born in the Bay Ridge area of Brooklyn, New York, to parents of Greek and Irish descent., Jason Calacanis is also one of the co-hosts of the All-In Podcast, along with Chamath Palihapitiya, David O. Sacks, and David Friedberg. The four hosts discuss what actions America should take to improve its current state. They explore various aspects of how to get America and the world back on track, with a focus on business and investment strategies., In the 1990s, Calacanis began his career as a reporter covering the internet industry in New York. We’d explore when and how he made his money over the years through his career journey below; Jason started a publishing company named Rising Tide Studios that produced both online and print magazines.]";
  <http://schema.org/thumbnailUrl> "https://media.earlynode.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Jason-Calacanis-1-scaled.jpg" .

